==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dewar flask
<hw>Dew"ar flask</hw></mhw>. <ety>[After Sir James
<etsep>Dewar</etsep>, British physicist.]</ety> <def>A double-walled
glass vessel for holding liquid air, liquid nitrogen, etc., having the
space between the walls exhausted so as to prevent conduction of heat,
and sometimes having the glass silvered to prevent absorption of radiant
heat; -- called also, according to the particular shape, <col><b>Dewar
bulb</b></col>, <col><b>Dewar tube</b></col>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dewberry</ent>⟦br⟧
